    • Constructor Detail

      • Projectile

        public Projectile(java.awt.Color color,
                  int x,
                  int y,
                  int w,
                  int h,
                  double vX,
                  int startup,
                  int maxDistance,
                  int facing,
                  int hitstun,
                  int blockstun,
                  double xKB,
                  double yKB,
                  BlockHeight blockHeight,
                  boolean transcendent,
                  boolean ko)
        Constructs a Projectile object.
        Parameters:
        color: - The color of the Projectile should be drawn in.
        x: - The projectile's initial horizontal position on the screen
        y: - The projectile's initial vertical position on the screen
        w: - The width of the Projectile
        h: - The height of the Projectile
        vX: - The horizontal velocity of the Projectile
        startup: - The number of frames it takes for the Projectile to be able to damage an opponent
        maxDistance: - The maximum distance the projectile can travel
        facing: - Which way the projectile moves, 1 for right, -1 for left
        hitstun: - The amount of time the opponent cannot act for when they get hit by this Projectile.
        blockstun: - The amount of time the opponent cannot act for when they block this Projectile
        xKB: - The amount of horizontal knockback inflicted on the opponent by getting hit by this Projectile.
        yKB: - The amount of vertical knockback inflicted on the opponent by getting hit by this Projectile.
        blockHeight: - Which way this Projectile needs to be blocked
        transcendent: - True if it should not interact with other projectiles, false if it should.
        ko: - Whether the move knocks out in the corner
